  "why": "The paper goes beyond simply reporting failure counts by characterizing how erroneous behaviors vary across different synthesized environmental conditions and by correlating these failures with neuron‐coverage measures (KMNC/NBC) and steering‐angle divergences. This constitutes partial diagnostic insight into the properties of the discovered failures (e.g., which style vectors and environmental types yield concentrated errors and higher coverage). However, the work stops short of linking these failure patterns to underlying model vulnerabilities—such as dataset bias, reliance on spurious features, or overfitting—and does not perform causal or root‐cause analysis of the errors.",
